has been available since Java 10, which it is.\\n\\nFor AgentTest, I might need to ensure InvocationTargetException is handled correctly and consider method accessibility with `setAccessible(true)`.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Inspecting methods and tests**\\n\\nI could use getDeclaredMethod and setAccessible, and I might need to apply the same for utility methods. Checking `shadowLoader.getClass().getDeclaredMethod(\\\"addOverrideClasspathEntry\\\"...` seems fine. \\n\\nNext, I need to inspect the constructor of the shadow class and the private method urlToDefineClass. For the `ShadowClassLoaderTest`, it looks like `shadowLoader.getResource(\\\"lombok/core/TypeLibrary.SCL.lombok\\\")` returns null because I'm skipping self. This indicates a bug, as we should retrieve the shadow class before adding the override or use a new loader for duplicate definitions. \\n\\nIt might actually be best to split this into two test methods. One for handling resource loading and overriding, and another for checking duplicates. Also, `getResource(\\\"lombok/core/Main.SCL.lombok\\\")` returns null after the override, so I need to ensure the second test uses a new loader for accessible resources. I'll edit accordingly and consider adding accessible methods in PatchFixesHider.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering method accessibility**\\n\\nI need to look into whether private LocalMethods methods aren't accessible for util.invokeMethod. The util.findMethod function returns getDeclaredMethod but doesn't set accessible for those methods. This means that invoking a private method from another class might throw an IllegalAccessException, resulting in a sneaky throw. I need to ensure that we handle this properly, perhaps by setting accessible to true to avoid any access issues when invoking those private methods.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_qbFHmHBizuYeTCtiflakTjZj|fc_0e0cded080c840030169f006711854819fb2ccf0197e4259aa", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.projectlombok/lombok/1.18.20/src/test/java/org_projectlombok/lombok/ShadowClassLoaderTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "public class ShadowClassLoaderTest {\n\n    @Test\n    void loadsResourcesClassesAndDuplicateDefinitions() throws Exception {\n        ClassLoader shadowLoader = newShadowClassLoader();\n\n        assertThat(shadowLoader.getResource(\"java/lang/String.class\")).isNotNull();\n        assertThat(Collections.list(shadowLoader.getResources(\"java/lang/String.class\"))).isNotEmpty();\n        assertThat(shadowLoader.loadClass(\"java.lang.String\")).isSameAs(String.class);\n\n        Method addOverrideClasspathEntry = declaredMethod(shadowLoader.getClass(), \"addOverrideClasspathEntry\", String.class);\n        Path overrideDirectory = Files.createTempDirectory(\"lombok-shadow-override\");\n        addOverrideClasspathEntry.invoke(shadowLoader, overrideDirectory.toString());\n        assertThat(shadowLoader.getResource(\"lombok/core/Main.SCL.lombok\")).isNull();\n\n        Method urlToDefineClass = declaredMethod(shadowLoader.getClass(), \"urlToDefineClass\", String.class, URL.class, boolean.class);\n        URL shadowClass = shadowLoader.getResource(\"lombok/core/TypeLibrary.SCL.lombok\");\n        assertThat(shadowClass).isNotNull();\n\n        Class<?> firstDefinition = (Class<?>) urlToDefineClass.invoke(shadowLoader, \"lombok.core.TypeLibrary\", shadowClass, false);\n        Class<?> duplicateDefinition = (Class<?>) urlToDefineClass.invoke(shadowLoader, \"lombok.core.TypeLibrary\", shadowClass, false);\n\n        assertThat(duplicateDefinition).isSameAs(firstDefinition);\n    }\n", "newText": "public class ShadowClassLoaderTest {\n\n    @Test\n    void loadsResourcesAndClassesThroughTheShadowLoader() throws Exception {\n        ClassLoader shadowLoader = newShadowClassLoader();\n\n        assertThat(shadowLoader.getResource(\"java/lang/String.class\")).isNotNull();\n        assertThat(Collections.list(shadowLoader.getResources(\"java/lang/String.class\"))).isNotEmpty();\n        assertThat(shadowLoader.loadClass(\"java.lang.String\")).isSameAs(String.class);\n\n        Method addOverrideClasspathEntry = declaredMethod(shadowLoader.getClass(), \"addOverrideClasspathEntry\", String.class);\n        Path overrideDirectory = Files.createTempDirectory(\"lombok-shadow-override\");\n        addOverrideClasspathEntry.invoke(shadowLoader, overrideDirectory.toString());\n\n        assertThat(shadowLoader.getResource(\"lombok/core/Main.SCL.lombok\")).isNull();\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void fallsBackToTheAlreadyDefinedClassWhenTheSameBytesAreDefinedTwice() throws Exception {\n        ClassLoader shadowLoader = newShadowClassLoader();\n        Method urlToDefineClass = declaredMethod(shadowLoader.getClass(), \"urlToDefineClass\", String.class, URL.class, boolean.class);\n        URL shadowClass = shadowLoader.getResource(\"lombok/core/TypeLibrary.SCL.lombok\");\n        assertThat(shadowClass).isNotNull();\n\n        Class<?> firstDefinition = (Class<?>) urlToDefineClass.invoke(shadowLoader, \"lombok.core.TypeLibrary\", shadowClass, false);\n        Class<?> duplicateDefinition = (Class<?>) urlToDefineClass.invoke(shadowLoader, \"lombok.core.TypeLibrary\", shadowClass, false);\n\n        assertThat(duplicateDefinition).isSameAs(firstDefinition);\n    }\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.4", "usage": {"input": 329, "output": 1652, "cacheRead": 55552, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 57533, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777337953597, "responseId": "resp_0e0cded080c840030169f00662a378819f9efc4e949118cc0c"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_qbFHmHBizuYeTCtiflakTjZj|fc_0e0cded080c840030169f006711854819fb2ccf0197e4259aa", "toolName": "edit", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully replaced 1 block(s) in tests/src/org.projectlombok/lombok/1.