tive tests like `Class.forName` and others may occur, there's potential for issues. The task clearly emphasizes not using reflection in tests unless necessary, which raises the need to minimize such instances to avoid failures during native execution. I'll need to rethink this approach.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing test reflection limits**\\n\\nI'm realizing that user-code-filter only includes `lombok.**`, which means test reflections might not gather metadata. If JUnit can register reflection, maybe that could help, but it seems I need a native test run for these tests. Direct reflection into library internals could cause failures if metadata isn't auto-registered. I considered options like using `MethodHandles.privateLookupIn`, but it still feels too reflective. Putting tests in the library package is against the rules. I may need to rethink how we handle package-private classes or explore other avenues.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Adjusting user-code-filter considerations**\\n\\nI see that the agent config depends on the JVM tests, and if the user-code-filter excludes tests, reflections from those tests won't be included. This could lead to native compile or runtime failures. I’m wondering if I should adjust the user-code-filter to include the test package, even though the user specifically asked to generate tests only and keep them outside library packages. Maybe I can modify the filter to accept a test package, like `org_projectlombok.lombok.**`, but I need to tread carefully with the rules here.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test package integration**\\n\\nI’m focusing on filtering to a tests package since native metadata for test reflection will be recorded. This might be necessary, but the task mentioned adding or refining tests. I’m wondering if the patch to the user-code-filter is linked to enabling the tests. Should I pursue that? I feel like it’s worth checking if other test projects include the test package in their user-code-filter. It seems like a valuable search!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_GqBMopNKmis4Mqgsv0ZQDkS5|fc_0e0cded080c840030169f006a1889c819f88e4ad714b8c627e", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg -n 'org_projectlombok|user-code-filter.json' tests/src -g 'user-code-filter.json' | head -n 40", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.4", "usage": {"input": 341, "output": 1157, "cacheRead": 61696, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 63194, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777337997480, "responseId": "resp_0e0cded080c840030169f0068e737c819f9aa867404ea3dfc1"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_GqBMopNKmis4Mqgsv0ZQDkS5|fc_0e0cded080c840030169f006a1889c819f88e4ad714b8c627e", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "(no output)"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777338018094}]}
