[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating ShadowClassLoader tests**\n\nI’m considering that the second test for ShadowClassLoader might define the class twice, which could potentially work but may be using some internal method reflectively. I'm not entirely sure if that’s the best approach. I think the first test could benefit from using new assertions to ensure accuracy and reliability. I'll need to check these assertions closely to see if they improve the test performance.\n\n**Inspecting potential compile errors**\n\nI need to check for compile errors related to the PrintStream constructor with charset, which might be available since JDK 10. That seems fine. I should also inspect EclipsePatcher to determine if fake instrumentation is possible. It's essential to read through the relevant methods to get a clear understanding. This process might take some time, but it feels necessary to clarify these details!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0e0cded080c840030169f006e3769c819fa6b6959e435cb57d\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp8Ab1FKXdTebdeHxyBotwkGgDBp-cM6gSUJ4AdbhuDfnqTWgPcqwqajtdfH7Vpi83S2vlmNe6t4cZ7JEdIVMnwa4B9Jo0i3-nTNdF-kYj2ISwsoucZkSfZUip2A-_YxAs-sAmX1Xi2Cww1y8OB8qF4fw03IHrXWPMkuCJ3X40r5IWTUH4nyWiE3fTLGn3hp8LvWbH2x1mD6o8IbWZwHIgtL2BZi0fBnEH8GfoqDLcufeaoEPgSg1M1fuIj8U_MUmFazuBfs8VAVRkcHfJ76A6qGFtVQ5gVNgI_YSMTHhcQ5f2-iJfVJqHkXWUqDulCNVo9hPv7twk5hrWPpYqev3e2NNuBkQWmYrATnff_kbwXJEF0WBzhZzeIz_2gJJWzBW5T2cWDHe7-hg7l8d28kqt0OsCStHqMC3zlzHNh21e6vxhi--jdsSC0hWdBg7jAxJA07CS9H60P8QFcEf4hVMbh72uz_nuxzyq3eR4RiQCAkTIZimMEdbxBX59OSedULmUpnxsNQ8ssWMvwFdFDXz3hCIDJUW8QAyVzf4MB-UXrtHclHRnS6u-yDBH6zgZ8NAhladTClW2X51jihNJTtg2J4_uWf7RqyRsdP9ajJCABNgfx-a8xobJJF71hUnekU1IDjrxn-AkFVnhRwJ8hAT1TYeHpSDRfxmhtlaYLgGVhxx6nxIIedyzNv4YbqhfHqPtVJXgcJpwPM3LoL6TnarDzS2now6cER2jqjg0_hlra_DOzcVCLxul29N-Dvhs14uwcLxckReKUjlbtqpu5B9BFLA3qU7Y2HEirL2HlKCSKE1y5cw7H0tAeFPffBGBOwq9vMk1ZQAU8pH57sein8jdG6